{
  "stem": "13315.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Joseph Brod.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "B-R-O-D.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Look, it was original, because it's a derivative, as I told you before, that those names were-- Jews, especially in the monarchy, Bohemian and so, they were forced-- only the oldest son in a family was permitted to marry legally and stay in the town as a denizen-- not citizen, denizen.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the youngest son, if he married here, to live and look for some other town  or village that would accept him as a denizen [? and ?] [? innocent. ?] So Brod-- what it meant there, ford.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like in Poland, brod means also a ford over a river.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they came from some town over-- on a ford.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they had only first names.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the new neighbors to distinguish them, they said, oh, he's from the brod.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then it became Brod.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's what it means.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what is your birth date and current age?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My birthday is June 2nd, '08.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the age is-- nearly 88.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Vienna, Austria.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No brothers, no sisters.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's name was Mathilde, born Vohryzek.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And father was Emil Brod.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was the second youngest son in a big family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And mother was the oldest daughter in the big family, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The early family life actually is hard to describe because, as a little boy, I had rickets.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the doctor didn't permit me to walk at all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was-- my locomotion was on one of those pot chambers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was the only thing that I could do, because they were afraid my legs would be crooked until about three-- three-- three and a half years.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then I could start walking.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then-- from then on, I was more or less of a loner, because father was always busy.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
